</div><p></p><p> On the interesting, but ultimately pointless, pollster’s question <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/boris-johnson/12039931/Boris-Johnson-The-only-reason-I-wouldnt-visit-some-parts-of-New-York-is-the-real-risk-of-meeting-Donald-Trump.html">“Who would you rather have a pint with?”</a> Boris will always come out on top. But I’m not convinced too many people ate their lunch on their lap on Sunday, glued to Sky News as they waited for white smoke to emerge from the chimney of Boris’s home. </p><p> If I’m wrong, and they were hanging on his every word, I’m not sure they would have been that impressed when Boris didn’t appear to know the name of the political group he’d aligned his entire political future with. “Vote Leave – or whatever the team is called,” as he put it. Really Boris? And you want me to dive headlong into the dark with you? Amusing? Possibly. Persuasive? Not-so-much. </p><p> <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/eureferendum/12166345/European-referendum-Michael-Gove-explains-why-Britain-should-leave-the-EU.html">Michael Gove is a far more dangerous opponent</a> and if Vote Leave have any sense, he’ll be given more campaign time than Boris. His long personal statement was a class apart. Where Boris was bumbling, he was articulate, measured and sincere. </p><p> He will also understand, perhaps better than Boris, what is required in the months ahead. To explain, in plain English, to a largely undecided and confused electorate what Brexit might mean to them, their families and their businesses. To answer questions like: “How will it work exactly?”, “How will it affect me and mine precisely?”. </p><p>
</p><aside class="tmg-particle pull-quote" data-data-uri="http://particle-api.eip.telegraph.co.uk/particles/0.1/9dbe686d-0a4d-4635-b40c-3875d739bae9" data-embeddable="0" data-html-uri="http://cf-particle-html.eip.telegraph.co.uk/9dbe686d-0a4d-4635-b40c-3875d739bae9.html" data-widget-size="responsive" data-widget-static="true" id="9dbe686d-0a4d-4635-b40c-3875d739bae9">
